						               													<description>BlazBlue: Chrono Phantasma, released in Japan as BlazBlue: Chronophantasma (&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#150;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#172;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#164;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#150;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#171;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#188; &amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#175;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#173;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#142;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#149;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#161;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#179;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#191;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#186;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#158; BureiBur&amp;#197;&amp;#171; Kuronofantazuma?), is a 2-D fighting game developed by Arc System Works. It is the third game of the Blazblue series, set after the events of BlazBlue: Continuum Shift. The game was originally to be released first as an arcade game in the fourth quarter of 2012, which was later pushed forward to November 2012. A PlayStation 3 version of the game was released in Japan on October 24, 2013, while it was released in the United States on March 25, 2014. Due to limited hardware and disc space on the Xbox 360, Chrono Phantasma is currently only available for PlayStation systems.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
										      				
		 			

			
		
